author: ULA ILNYTZKY
title: Titanic's last lunch menu auctioned for $88,000
text:
NEW YORK (AP) — The Titanic's last lunch menu has sold at auction for $88,000.
Online New York auctioneer Lion Heart Autographs offered it along with two other previously unknown artifacts from Lifeboat 1 on Wednesday.
The menu was saved by a passenger who escaped in the so-called "Money Boat" before the ocean liner went down in 1912. The lifeboat got its nickname because of unfounded rumors that one of the first-class passengers bribed crew members to row away with 12 people on a boat with a capacity of 40.
A letter by one of its survivors written six months after the disaster fetched $7,500.
A printed ticket from the Titanic's opulent Turkish baths that recorded a person's weight when seated in a specially designed chair brought $11,000.
